## 🔄 WebSocket Connection Logic

The WebSocket now correctly constructs URLs based on the API configuration:
```typescript
const apiBaseUrl = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:8101'
const wsHost = apiBaseUrl.replace(/^https?:\/\//, '').replace(/:\d+$/, '') + 
               (apiBaseUrl.includes(':8101') ? ':8101' : ':8100')
const wsUrl = `${wsProtocol}//${wsHost}/ws/plans/${planId}`
```

